<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,222,1543]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
Although the original 
<typeStatus box="[407,455,223,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">type</typeStatus>
locality was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stoll" box="[722,849,222,247]" firstAuthor="Stoll" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="165 - 252" refId="ref32635" refString="Stoll, C (1780 - 1782) In: Cramer, P. (Ed.), De uitlandische Kapellen voorkomende in de drie Waereld-Deelen Asia, Africa en America. Papillons exotiques des trois parties du monde l'Asie, l'Afrique et l'Amerique. 4 (26 / 28), (29 / 31), (32 / 34). J. S. Baalde Amsteldam, Barthelemy Wild. Utrecht, pp. 29 - 90, pls. 305 - 336 (1780); pp. 91 - 164, pls. 337 - 372 (1781), pp. 165 - 252, pls. 373 - 400 (1782)." type="journal article" year="1780">
Stoll (
<number box="[792,849,223,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1781.0" valueMax="1782.0" valueMin="1780.0">
<date box="[792,849,223,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1780" valueMax="1782">1780</date>
</number>
</bibRefCitation>
–1782) as 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1070,222,247]" name="Suriname" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, this was an error, and the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,223,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">type</typeStatus>
locality is accepted as West Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery" box="[574,800,258,283]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ackery" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29534" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (Eds.) (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, 803 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Ackery 
<emphasis box="[669,721,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[740,800,258,283]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the only species of the genus in West Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[158,303,294,319]" firstAuthor="Larsen" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref31586" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen 
<number box="[243,303,294,319]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and its distribution extends east to 
<collectingCountry box="[707,827,295,319]" name="Cameroon" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[838,1052,294,319]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1138,294,319]" name="Gabon" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Gabon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1191,1312,295,319]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ackery" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29534" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (Eds.) (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, 803 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Ackery 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[188,246,330,355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[258,403,330,355]" firstAuthor="Larsen" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref31586" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen 
<number box="[342,403,330,355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Heath, A. &amp; Newport, M. A. &amp; Hancock, D." box="[422,655,330,355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref30712" refString="Heath, A., Newport, M. A. &amp; Hancock, D. (2002) The Butterflies of Zambia. African Butterfly Research Institute and The Lepidopterists' Society of Africa, Nairobi, 137 pp. + CD." type="book" year="2002">
Heath 
<emphasis box="[497,546,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
.’s (
<number box="[588,647,331,355]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
record from 
<collectingCountry box="[804,890,330,355]" name="Zambia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Zambia</collectingCountry>
(‘Hillwood (Ikelenge) (ABRI)’) was based on a misidentification for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[387,503,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[387,503,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[548,665,367,391]" name="Cameroon" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[719,794,367,391]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Congo</collectingCountry>
its range overlaps with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[1062,1178,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[1062,1178,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which for many years was considered a subspecies. In his simplified provisional check-list of the butterflies of the Afrotropical region, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carcasson" box="[151,349,439,463]" firstAuthor="Carcasson" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29877" refString="Carcasson, R. H. (1981) Collins Handguide to the Butterflies of Africa. Collins, London, 188 pp." type="book" year="1981">
Carcasson (
<number box="[283,341,439,463]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
first treated 
<taxonomicName authority="Riley" authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[498,652,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[498,583,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">reducta</emphasis>
Riley
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species separate from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[1034,1139,439,462]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1139,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but gave no explanation. This situation remained unchanged when Carcasson’s catalogue was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery" box="[1094,1329,474,499]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ackery" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29534" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (Eds.) (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, 803 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Ackery 
<emphasis box="[1185,1235,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1261,1321,474,499]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and was endorsed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" box="[294,454,510,535]" firstAuthor="Larsen" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref31586" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen (
<number box="[385,446,510,535]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Given that the two species overlap in 
<collectingCountry box="[887,1004,511,535]" name="Cameroon" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[1099,1177,511,535]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Congo</collectingCountry>
, their separation seems 
<emphasis box="[151,237,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">a priori</emphasis>
to be justified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,222,1543]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
Most of 
<bibRefCitation author="Riley's" box="[296,458,582,607]" firstAuthor="Riley's" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="281" refId="ref32184" refString="Riley, N. D. (1925) A revision of the continental African species of the genus Artitropa (Lep. Hesperiidae). Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1925, 281 - 288, plate 35. http: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1925. tb 02864. x" type="journal article" year="1925">
Riley’s (
<number box="[392,450,582,607]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
information on the early stages of ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[867,970,583,606]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[867,970,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is, given the locality (
<collectingCountry box="[1234,1327,582,607]" name="Uganda" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Uganda</collectingCountry>
), actually referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[288,404,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[288,404,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which Riley treated as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[857,961,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[857,961,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, Riley goes on to point out that the early stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[359,461,655,678]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[359,461,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar based on preserved material from Lagos in the Oxford University Museum. Riley does not explicitly state the food plant of the Lagos material, which he states comprises a male and five females reared by Dr. W.A. Lamborn. 
<collectionCode box="[590,671,727,751]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">MJWC</collectionCode>
examined this material in HEC; it actually comprises four females from Dr Lamborn, two of which were reared from pupae, all from near Oni, 
<quantity box="[1042,1140,762,787]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1265408" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" unit="mi" value="70.0">70 miles</quantity>
east of Lagos (cf. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchholzi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Gamia buchholzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above), and two males and a female caught in Lagos by J.A. de Gaye in 
<number box="[1098,1157,799,823]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1912.0">1912</number>
. The two reared females were collected as pupae ‘in forest, 
<date box="[550,657,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1911-09">
Sep 
<number box="[600,657,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1911.0">1911</number>
</date>
, and there is no indication as to the food plant. There are associated emerged pupae for both, of which one has the associated cast final caterpillar skin and head capsule. The head markings and spot on T 
<number box="[419,429,907,931]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1.0">1</number>
are comparable to those shown below for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[905,1021,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[905,1021,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1035,1202,906,931]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 18" captionStart-1="FIGURE 19" captionStart-2="FIGURE 20" captionStart-3="FIGURE 21" captionStartId-0="21.[151,250,1894,1916]" captionStartId-1="22.[151,250,956,978]" captionStartId-2="22.[151,250,1851,1873]" captionStartId-3="23.[151,250,1466,1488]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,1420,1870]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,639,931]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,1212,1826]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1436,663,1441]" captionTargetId-0="figure@21.[151,1436,1420,1871]" captionTargetId-1="figure@22.[151,1436,639,931]" captionTargetId-2="figure@22.[151,1436,1212,1826]" captionTargetId-3="figure@23.[151,1436,663,1441]" captionTargetPageId-0="21" captionTargetPageId-1="22" captionTargetPageId-2="22" captionTargetPageId-3="23" captionText-0="FIGURE 18. Final instar caterpillars of Artitropa reducta, collected as small caterpillar on D. steudneri, Kigale, Rwanda, 7 Feb 1990; moulted to final instar 21 Feb; photographed 22 Feb, 37 mm; pupated 4 Mar; 90 / 201 A: 1, dorsolateral view; 2, detail of head, anterolateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 19. Final instar caterpillar of Artitropa reducta collected on either Dracaena fragrans or D. steudneri, western Kenya [SCC]. 1, dorsal view, 1 Jan 2004; 2, detail of head, anterior view, 27 Sep 2004." captionText-2="FIGURE 20. Ovum and caterpillar of Artitropa reducta, collected on Dracaena mannii, Lisombo Stream, north-west Zambia [TCEC]. 1, ovum, dorsal view, 18 Nov 2005; 2, lateral view, 21 May 2000; 3, head and anterior segments, final instar caterpillar, dorsal view; 3 Nov 2004. 4, head, final instar caterpillar, anterior view, 11 May 2000; 5, final instar caterpillar, dorsolateral view, 11 May 2000." captionText-3="FIGURE 21. Ovum and caterpillars of Artitropa reducta, collected on Dracaena mannii, Rondo Plateau, south-eastern Tanzania [TCEC]. 1, ovum, dorsal view 19 Feb 2001; 2, ovum, lateral view, 19 Feb 2001. 3, final instar, detail of head, anterior view, 9 Feb 2005; 4, detail of head, anterior view, 28 Mar 1998; 5, final instar dorsal view, 9 Feb 2005." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/253551/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/253552/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/253553/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/253554/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
Figures 
<number box="[1128,1202,907,931]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,222,1543]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
The food plant records of 
<bibRefCitation author="Le Pelley" box="[487,677,942,967]" firstAuthor="Le Pelley" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref31613" refString="Le Pelley, R. H. (1959) Agricultural Insects of East Africa. East Africa High Commission, Nairobi, 307 pp." type="book" year="1959">
Le Pelley (
<number box="[608,668,942,967]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1959.0">1959</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sevastopulo" box="[688,900,942,967]" firstAuthor="Sevastopulo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="131" refId="ref32345" refString="Sevastopulo, D. G. (1974) Butterflies of the Shimba Hills. Entomologist's Record and Journal of Variation, 86, 131 - 136." type="journal article" year="1974">Sevastopulo (1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sevastopulo" box="[910,969,942,967]" firstAuthor="Sevastopulo" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="147 - 172" refId="ref32373" refString="Sevastopulo, D. G. (1975) Hesperiidae. In: Sevastopulo, D. G. (1975 - 1978) A list of the food-plants of East African Macrolepidoptera. Bulletin of the Amateur Entomologists' Society, 34, pp. 131 - 132. [pp. 84 - 92, 124 - 132, 175 - 184; 35, pp. 94 - 100, 177 - 195; 36, pp. 45 - 50; 37, pp. 147 - 172, 202 - 216]" type="journal article" year="1975">1975</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Someren" box="[989,1222,943,967]" firstAuthor="Van Someren" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="315" refId="ref33112" refString="Van Someren, V. G. L. (1974) List of foodplants of some East African Rhopalocera, with notes on the early stages of some Lycaenidae. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 28, 315 - 331." type="journal article" year="1974">
Van Someren (
<number box="[1153,1213,943,967]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1974.0">1974</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carcasson" box="[1233,1432,943,967]" firstAuthor="Carcasson" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29877" refString="Carcasson, R. H. (1981) Collins Handguide to the Butterflies of Africa. Collins, London, 188 pp." type="book" year="1981">
Carcasson (
<number box="[1363,1423,943,967]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery" box="[151,380,978,1003]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ackery" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref29534" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (Eds.) (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, 803 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Ackery 
<emphasis box="[240,288,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[311,371,978,1003]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Heath" box="[391,606,978,1003]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Heath" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" refId="ref30712" refString="Heath, A., Newport, M. A. &amp; Hancock, D. (2002) The Butterflies of Zambia. African Butterfly Research Institute and The Lepidopterists' Society of Africa, Nairobi, 137 pp. + CD." type="book" year="2002">
Heath 
<emphasis box="[466,515,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[537,598,979,1003]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, etc. are considered to refer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[951,1066,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[951,1066,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,222,1543]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
In 
<number box="[229,288,1015,1039]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1994.0">1994</number>
, 
<collectionCode box="[300,381,1015,1039]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">MJWC</collectionCode>
found a dead final instar caterpillar and a pupa killed by a parasitoid with the cast final instar skin on a 
<taxonomicName box="[260,372,1052,1075]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[260,372,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. at Toumodi, near Yamoussoukro, 
<collectingCountry box="[800,954,1050,1075]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
. The caterpillar head was similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,269,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(below): 
<number box="[381,430,1086,1111]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="3.65">3.65</number>
x 
<quantity box="[462,540,1087,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2mm</quantity>
wide x high; pale brown with yellow flush on face; rugose, no obvious setae; large oval dark spot on each epicranium, the lower inner margin adjacent to upper adfrontals; posterior margin, sutures, adfrontals and frons all ground colour; pronotum pale with a dark spot laterally. The pupa was similar to those of other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[314,417,1195,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[314,417,1195,1218]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Artitropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.: unmarked pale brown; erect pale brown setae in small patch on T 
<number box="[1227,1239,1195,1219]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="3.0">3</number>
dorsum, directed backwards, and in line down centre of eye. The pupa had a single 
<quantity box="[885,964,1230,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6mm</quantity>
diameter parasitoid emergence hole cut in the front of the head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,222,1543]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
The first unequivocal published food plant record for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[805,909,1303,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[805,909,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Vuattoux" box="[1023,1208,1303,1327]" firstAuthor="Vuattoux" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="562" refId="ref33184" refString="Vuattoux, R. (1999) Les lepidopteres hesperiides de la Station de Lamto (Cote d'Ivoire). Lambillionea, 94, 562 - 568." type="journal article" year="1999">
Vuattoux (
<number box="[1142,1200,1303,1327]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who reared a dozen on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1874" box="[187,301,1340,1363]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mannii">
<emphasis box="[187,301,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">D. mannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1874" box="[350,498,1340,1363]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrottetii">
<emphasis box="[350,498,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">D. perrottetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). We can find no significant differences between the early stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[1283,1387,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1387,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[254,374,1374,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis box="[254,374,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[391,561,1374,1399]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 18" captionStart-1="FIGURE 19" captionStart-2="FIGURE 20" captionStart-3="FIGURE 21" captionStartId-0="21.[151,250,1894,1916]" captionStartId-1="22.[151,250,956,978]" captionStartId-2="22.[151,250,1851,1873]" captionStartId-3="23.[151,250,1466,1488]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,1420,1870]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,639,931]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,1212,1826]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1436,663,1441]" captionTargetId-0="figure@21.[151,1436,1420,1871]" captionTargetId-1="figure@22.[151,1436,639,931]" captionTargetId-2="figure@22.[151,1436,1212,1826]" captionTargetId-3="figure@23.[151,1436,663,1441]" captionTargetPageId-0="21" captionTargetPageId-1="22" captionTargetPageId-2="22" captionTargetPageId-3="23" captionText-0="FIGURE 18. Final instar caterpillars of Artitropa reducta, collected as small caterpillar on D. steudneri, Kigale, Rwanda, 7 Feb 1990; moulted to final instar 21 Feb; photographed 22 Feb, 37 mm; pupated 4 Mar; 90 / 201 A: 1, dorsolateral view; 2, detail of head, anterolateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 19. Final instar caterpillar of Artitropa reducta collected on either Dracaena fragrans or D. steudneri, western Kenya [SCC]. 1, dorsal view, 1 Jan 2004; 2, detail of head, anterior view, 27 Sep 2004." captionText-2="FIGURE 20. Ovum and caterpillar of Artitropa reducta, collected on Dracaena mannii, Lisombo Stream, north-west Zambia [TCEC]. 1, ovum, dorsal view, 18 Nov 2005; 2, lateral view, 21 May 2000; 3, head and anterior segments, final instar caterpillar, dorsal view; 3 Nov 2004. 4, head, final instar caterpillar, anterior view, 11 May 2000; 5, final instar caterpillar, dorsolateral view, 11 May 2000." captionText-3="FIGURE 21. Ovum and caterpillars of Artitropa reducta, collected on Dracaena mannii, Rondo Plateau, south-eastern Tanzania [TCEC]. 1, ovum, dorsal view 19 Feb 2001; 2, ovum, lateral view, 19 Feb 2001. 3, final instar, detail of head, anterior view, 9 Feb 2005; 4, detail of head, anterior view, 28 Mar 1998; 5, final instar dorsal view, 9 Feb 2005." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/253551/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/253552/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/253553/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/253554/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
Figures 
<number box="[487,561,1375,1399]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21</number>
</figureCitation>
). SCC has found early stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1782" box="[950,1055,1375,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comus">
<emphasis box="[950,1055,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">A. comus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several countries in west and central Africa on a variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[481,593,1412,1435]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[481,593,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., including exotics, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ker Gawl" authorityYear="1808" baseAuthorityName="L." box="[979,1110,1411,1435]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrans">
<emphasis box="[979,1110,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">D. fragrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1229,1410,1435]" name="Liberia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Liberia</collectingCountry>
, at Obudu, eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,235,1446,1471]" name="Nigeria" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<date box="[252,382,1446,1471]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2007-04">
April 
<number box="[324,382,1447,1471]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</date>
) and in 
<collectingCountry box="[482,602,1447,1471]" name="Cameroon" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1874" box="[615,731,1447,1470]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mannii">
<emphasis box="[615,731,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">D. mannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[773,846,1446,1471]" name="Ghana" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[907,1063,1446,1471]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1821" baseAuthorityName="Willd." box="[1128,1254,1446,1471]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis box="[1128,1254,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">D. arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Bioko (
<date pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2011-12">
Dec 
<number box="[151,211,1483,1507]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</date>
). They can be horticultural pests of ornamental 
<taxonomicName box="[766,878,1484,1507]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[766,878,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and adults have been observed to come to light.
</paragraph>
